>>>>>>> There are loads of ways you can get involved and help those living
with diabetes in Wales. No matter how much time you have or how involved you
want to be, this is the place where you can find out more about all the
opportunities available for you to make a difference to people living with
>>>>>>> Volunteers and fundraisers the Baldwins have worked tirelessly to
raise awareness of the 4 Ts (Toilet, Thirsty, Tired, Thinner) since losing
their teenage son Peter to undiagnosed Type 1 diabetes. They have also raised
over £20,000 for Diabetes UK. Pictured above is Beth Baldwin holding her Pride
of Britain award with her husband Stuart and their daughter.
>>>>>>> From giving your time as a Media Volunteer to making people aware of
their risk of developing Type 2 diabetes as a Know Your Risk Volunteer at one
of our Roadshows find out more about our volunteering opportunities in Wales.
>>>>>>> You can be creative and Fundraise Your Way with our support, or you
can take part in an organised local event to raise money for Diabetes UK
Cymru. Find out more and start raising vital funds.
>>>>>>> Add your voice to help drive our campaigns work forward with specific
actions by joining our Diabetes Voices network. If you feel passionately about
a particular issue we aren't currently addressing we can support you in
>>>>>>> See this page in Welsh - I weld yn Gymraeg
